---
const { tabText, home = false } = Astro.props;
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link rel="sitemap" href="/sitemap-index.xml" />
  <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.png" sizes="any">
  <!-- <link rel="icon" href="/icon.svg" type="image/svg+xml"> -->
  <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/apple-touch-icon.png">
  <link rel="manifest" href="/site.webmanifest" />
  <link href="/fontawesome/css/fontawesome.min.css" rel="stylesheet" />
  <link href="/fontawesome/css/brands.min.css" rel="stylesheet" />

  <meta name="msapplication-TileColor" content="#5cebdf" />
  <meta name="theme-color" content="#ffffff" />
  <title>{tabText}</title>

  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/global.css">
  <style is:global>

    @font-face {
      font-family: KenyanCoffeeRegular;
      src: url(/fonts/kenyan_coffee_rg.otf);
    }

    @font-face {
      font-family: videotype;
      src: url(/fonts/videotype.otf);
    }

    .ccc-icon-bar {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: row;
      justify-content: center;
      column-gap: 25px;
      margin-top: 30px;
    }

    .ccc-icon {
      font-size: 65px;
      color: #2d0203;
    }

    .ccc-icon:hover {
      cursor: pointer;
      color: #4d2223;
    }

    .bio-image {
      background-position: center;
      background-size: cover;
      background-repeat: no-repeat;
      width: 400px;
      height: 400px;
      position: relative;
      background-color: #222;
    }

    .bio-image.nuke {
      background-image: url(/images/nuke.jpg);
    }

    .bio-image.folt {
      background-image: url(/images/folt_and_pandar.jpg);
    }

    .bio-image.pandar {
      background-image: url(/images/pandar_and_folt.jpg);
    }

    .bio-image.sincere {
      background-image: url(/images/sincere.jpg);
    }

    .ccc-grid-item_nametag {
      position: absolute;
      bottom: 0;
      left: 0;
      width: 100%;
      text-align: center;
      height: 35px;
      background-color: #003600;
      color: #fff;
      font-weight: bold;
      line-height: 31px;
      font-family: videotype, sans-serif;
      font-size: 24px;
      box-shadow: 0px 2px 4px #222;
    }

    .ccc-grid {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: row;
      column-gap: 25px;
      row-gap: 25px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      justify-content: center;
    }

    .ccc-grid-item {
      box-shadow: 1px 1px 4px #222;
      background-color: #efefef;
      border-radius: 25px;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .ccc-grid-item_text {
      max-width: 350px;
      padding: 15px 10px 25px 10px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .ccc-h2 {
      text-align: center;
      border-top: 2px solid #003600;
      border-bottom: 2px solid #003600;
      color: #317620;
      text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px #222;
      font-family: KenyanCoffeeRegular, sans-serif;
      font-size: 72px;
      letter-spacing: 2px;
      position: relative;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    .ccc-h2_backdrop {
      position: absolute;
      top: 0;
      left: 0;
      height: 100%;
      width: 100%;
      background-color: #444;
      opacity: .5;
    }

    .ccc-text-content {
      padding: 30px;
      text-align: center;
      border-radius: 25px;
      background-color: rgb(239, 239, 239, .5);
      margin: 0 20px;
    }

    .ccc-banner {
      height: 480px;
      width: auto;
      background-image: url(/images/ccc_logo_source_rectrangle_crop.png);
      background-position: center;
      background-repeat: no-repeat;
      background-size: cover;
      box-shadow: 2px 2px 4px #222;
    }

    .content-container {
      max-width: 1445px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: center;
    }

    :root {
    
      --heading: var(--neutral-dark-900);
      --text: var(--neutral-dark-900);
      --text-muted: var(--neutral-dark-600);
      --primary: var(--blue-700);
      --primary-darker: var(--blue-800);
      --highlight: var(--teal-300);
      --button:var(--neutral-light-000);
      --lightBorder: var(--neutral-light-200);
      --light: var(--neutral-light-100);
      --white: var(--neutral-light-000);
      --card-radius: var(--border-radius-3);
      --font-primary: Pacaembu, sans-serif;
      --font-secondary: Mulish, sans-serif;
    }

    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    html,
    body {
      color: var(--text);
      font-family: var(--font-secondary);
      font-size: 18px;
      line-height: 1.45;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      background-color: #CB9472;
      padding-bottom: 50px;
    }

    body {
      display: block;
      justify-content: center;
      min-height: 100vh;
    }

    h1, h2, h3 {
      font-family: var(--font-primary);
    }

    a:link,
    a:visited {
      color: var(--text);
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-decoration-color: var(--text);
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    a:hover,
    a:focus {
      text-decoration-color: var(--highlight);
    }

    main {
      background: var(--light);
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      margin-top: 3rem;
      padding: 2rem max(5vw, 50vw - 60ch / 2);
      width: 100vw;
      border-style: none;
    }

    .sr-only:not(:focus):not(:active) {
      clip: rect(0 0 0 0);
      clip-path: inset(50%);
      height: 1px;
      overflow: hidden;
      position: absolute;
      white-space: nowrap;
      width: 1px;
    }

    .button,
    a.button {
      background: var(--primary);
      border-radius: 4px;
      color: var(--white);
      display: inline-block;
      font-weight: 800;
      padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
      text-decoration: none;
      width: max-content;
      transition-duration: .2s;
      text-decoration: none;
      margin-top: auto;
    }

    a.button:hover,
    a.button:focus,
    .button:hover,
    .button:focus {
      background: var(--primary-darker);
    }


    .container,
    .footer {
      margin: 0 auto;
      text-align: center;
      width: min(90vw, 900px);
    }

    .container {
      /* background-image: url("/images/ccc_logo_source_rectrangle_crop.png");
      background-repeat: no-repeat;
      background-size: contain;
      width: 100%;
      height: 400px; */
    }

    .heading {
      color: var(--heading);
      font-size: 2.5rem;
      margin: 0;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .footer {
      color: var(--text-muted);
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      margin-top: 4rem;
    }

    .footer a {
      color: inherit;
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    .footer a:focus,
    .footer a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }

    .footer ul {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      list-style-type: none;
    }

    .footer li {
      margin: 0 1em;
    }

    .heart {
      display: inline-block;
      vertical-align: top;
      width: 1.1rem;
    }

    .heart img {
      display: block;
      width: 100%;
    }
  </style>
  <script>
    window['ccc'] = {};

    const ccc = window['ccc'];

    ccc.goto = goto;

    function goto(urlName) {
      const urls = {
        'twitter': 'https://x.com/TheCannCoffCrew',
        'instagram': 'https://www.instagram.com/cannabiscoffeecrew'
      };

      window.open(urls[urlName]);
    }
  </script>
</head>

<body>
  <div class="content-container">
    <header class="ccc-banner"></header>
    <div class="ccc-icon-bar">
      <a href="https://x.com/TheCannCoffCrew">
        <i class="ccc-icon fa-brands fa-x-twitter"></i>
      </a>
      <a href="https://www.instagram.com/cannabiscoffeecrew">
        <i class="ccc-icon fa-brands fa-instagram"></i>
      </a>
    </div>
    <h2 class="ccc-h2" style={{ marginTop: '30px' }}>About Us</h2>
    <div class="ccc-text-content">
      Welcome to the Cannabis Coffee Crew, where deep conversations brew over a cup of coffee and a cloud of cannabis smoke. We are a group of passionate hosts who dive into everything from philosophical musings to conspiracy theories, always with an open mind and a dash of humor.

      Our goal is simple: to spark thought, question the norm, and connect with listeners who enjoy exploring life’s deeper, and sometimes stranger, sides. Whether you’re here for a thought-provoking debate or just to relax and enjoy the ride, we’re glad to have you with us on this journey. Tune in, grab a cup (and a puff), and let’s dive into the unknown together.
    </div>
    <h2 class="ccc-h2">Meet the Crew</h2>
    <div class="ccc-grid">
      <div class="ccc-grid-item">
        <div class="bio-image nuke">
          <div class="ccc-grid-item_nametag">TheBipolarNuke</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ccc-grid-item_text">
          Hey everyone, I'm TJ, but around here you might know me as TheBipolarNuke, or just Nuke. I'm originally from the quiet countryside of South Carolina, where I first learned to love the simple things in life—but my journey since then has been anything but simple.
          <br/><br/>
          I spent six years in the Navy as a nuclear machinist mate, working on reactors aboard aircraft carriers. It was an experience that taught me resilience, discipline, and the value of a good laugh during tough times. After my time in the Navy, I welcomed my amazing son into the world. Life only got better from there when I met my wonderful wife, who brought three more incredible children into my life.
          <br/><br/>
          Since then, I've transitioned from working with nuclear reactors to working behind the camera. I've been a video editor for a major news organization and a video producer for a large radio station upstate. These roles let me tap into my creative side, telling stories through the lens and bringing ideas to life on screen.
          <br/><br/>
          I love gaming, spending time with family and friends, and diving into deep, meaningful conversations—the kind that stick with you long after they're over.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ccc-grid-item">
        <div class="bio-image folt">
          <div class="ccc-grid-item_nametag">Folterung</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ccc-grid-item_text">
          Hey there! I'm Kevin Warnock, but you might know me as Folterung, or simply Folt, Folter, or Kev. I'm one of the hosts of the Cannabis Coffee Crew.
          <br/><br/>
          By day, I'm a Senior Software Engineer and Software Solutions Architect, and I'm also an author—but my passions don't stop there. When I'm not in front of a computer, you'll probably find me with a hammer at the forge, diving into blacksmithing, or exploring digital art. I love working with my hands, whether it’s crafting something physical or creating a digital masterpiece.
          <br/><br/>
          Music is my constant companion; I have a soundtrack for life that fuels my energy and creativity. Whether I'm coding, relaxing, or brainstorming new podcast ideas, there's always a beat playing to match my mood.
          <br/><br/>
          I'm 38 years old, happily married for 15 years, and a proud father of four incredible kids. I'm thrilled to share my thoughts and opinions on the Cannabis Coffee Crew, but even more, I love hearing from others and getting into real conversations. I can't wait to chat with our listeners and dive into all the wild, thoughtful, and fun topics we explore together.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ccc-grid-item">
        <div class="bio-image pandar">
          <div class="ccc-grid-item_nametag">Pandar</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ccc-grid-item_text">
          Hey Y'all! I'm Amanda Warnock, but you can call me Mandar_el_Pandar or just Pandar. Some people even call me Panda, but definitely never Mandy! I'm one of those people who love exploring creativity in every corner of life, whether it's crafting, cooking, or diving into an imaginative story.
          <br/><br/>
          Before life brought me into the world of homeschooling and writing, I spent years managing teams and serving tables, learning all about hard work and hustle as a General Manager at Domino's and as a waitress. Then, motherhood took over, and I embraced every bit of it. For over ten years, I've been a stay-at-home mom, raising my amazing kids while also channeling my creative energy into starting a custom home bakery—Panda Cakes. There, I got to combine my passion for baking with artistic designs, making cakes that were not just tasty but also little pieces of art.
          <br/><br/>
          These days, I'm balancing my roles as a homeschooling mom, an author and wife for 15 years as I continue my love for creativity. Whether it's doodling, working on diamond art, crafting with my Cricut, or whipping up some bomb-ass Southern cooking, I'm always finding ways to express myself. 
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ccc-grid-item">
        <div class="bio-image sincere">
          <div class="ccc-grid-item_nametag">Sincere_</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ccc-grid-item_text">
          Hey Y'all! I'm Amanda Warnock, but you can call me Mandar_el_Pandar or just Pandar. Some people even call me Panda, but definitely never Mandy! I'm one of those people who love exploring creativity in every corner of life, whether it's crafting, cooking, or diving into an imaginative story.
          <br/><br/>
          Before life brought me into the world of homeschooling and writing, I spent years managing teams and serving tables, learning all about hard work and hustle as a General Manager at Domino's and as a waitress. Then, motherhood took over, and I embraced every bit of it. For over ten years, I've been a stay-at-home mom, raising my amazing kids while also channeling my creative energy into starting a custom home bakery—Panda Cakes. There, I got to combine my passion for baking with artistic designs, making cakes that were not just tasty but also little pieces of art.
          <br/><br/>
          These days, I'm balancing my roles as a homeschooling mom, an author and wife for 15 years as I continue my love for creativity. Whether it's doodling, working on diamond art, crafting with my Cricut, or whipping up some bomb-ass Southern cooking, I'm always finding ways to express myself. 
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
